src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7103:/// Unified REML/LAML evaluation.
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7106:/// - Gaussian REML with profiled scale
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7107:/// - Non-Gaussian LAML with fixed dispersion
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7109:/// - Any family (Gaussian, GLM, GAMLSS, survival, link wiggles)
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7111:/// Cost and gradient share intermediates by construction — they are computed
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7113:/// penalty derivatives, and the same coefficients. Drift between cost and
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7114:/// gradient is structurally impossible because there is no second function.
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7119:///   int exp(-F(beta)) dbeta  ~  exp(-F(beta_hat)) * (2pi)^{p/2} / sqrt(|H_obs|)
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7120:/// requires H_obs = nabla^2 F(beta_hat), the **observed** (actual) Hessian at
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7123:/// surrogate rather than the true Laplace/LAML criterion.
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7125:/// For this evaluator, the `solution.hessian_op` MUST encode log|H_obs| and
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7128:/// observed-information weights W_obs = W_Fisher - (y-mu)*B at the mode.
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7131:/// - The inner P-IRLS solver may use Fisher scoring (expected information)
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7133:/// - The outer REML criterion uses the observed Hessian at that mode.
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7134:/// This is correct because the inner algorithm is just a solver; only the
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7135:/// outer log|H| and trace terms define the Laplace approximation.
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7137:/// For canonical links (for example logit-Binomial and log-Poisson), observed
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7138:/// equals expected, so no correction is needed. For non-canonical links
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7139:/// (including probit, cloglog, SAS, mixture/flexible, and Gamma-log), the observed weight includes a
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7141:///   W_obs = W_Fisher - (y - mu) * B,
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7143:/// and the c/d arrays (dW/deta, d^2W/deta^2) similarly include observed
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7144:/// corrections. These are computed by `compute_observed_hessian_curvature_arrays`
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7145:/// in pirls.rs and flow through `PirlsResult` into the `InnerSolution`.
src/solver/reml/unified.rs:7148:/// - `solution`: The converged inner state (beta_hat, H_obs, penalties, corrections).
