   216	// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
   217	// Unified likelihood specification (in-progress migration)
   218	// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
   219	//
   220	// The codebase historically carries two parallel selectors:
   221	//
   222	//   * `LikelihoodFamily` — a flat enum mixing response distribution and link
   223	//     (e.g. `BinomialLogit`, `BinomialProbit`, `PoissonLog`).
   224	//   * `InverseLink` — a parameterized inverse-link selector (Standard,
   225	//     LatentCLogLog, Sas, BetaLogistic, Mixture).
   226	//
   227	// These two have to be kept consistent at every call site, which has caused
   228	// real drift bugs. The principled refactor is:
   229	//
   230	//   pub struct LikelihoodSpec { response: ResponseFamily, link: InverseLink }
   231	//
   232	// where `ResponseFamily` is a pure distribution selector
   233	// (`Gaussian | Binomial | Poisson | Gamma | RoystonParmar`) and every existing
   234	// `LikelihoodFamily` variant decomposes uniquely into the (response, link)
   235	// pair.
   236	//
   237	// MIGRATION PLAN (multi-phase):
   238	//
   239	//   Phase 1 (LANDED):
   240	//     - Introduce `ResponseFamily` and `LikelihoodSpec` alongside the legacy
   241	//       `LikelihoodFamily`.
   242	//     - Bidirectional conversion: `From<LikelihoodFamily> for LikelihoodSpec`
   243	//       (total) and `TryFrom<LikelihoodSpec> for LikelihoodFamily` (fails on
   244	//       (response, link) pairs that have no legacy variant — currently only
   245	//       Royston-Parmar with a non-identity link).
   246	//     - Mirror the 7 typed predicates on `LikelihoodSpec` so leaf modules can
   247	//       switch over without losing semantics.
   248	//     - Compatibility shim only. Zero behavior change. `cargo check` clean.
   249	//
   250	//   Phase 2 (LANDED, demonstration):
   251	//     - Migrated `src/families/family_meta.rs` and
   252	//       `src/families/survival_predict.rs` — the two smallest leaf modules — to
   253	//       use `LikelihoodSpec` predicates internally while their public APIs
   254	//       still accept `LikelihoodFamily` (bridged via `.into()` at entry).
   255	//
   256	//   Phase 3 (FUTURE):
   257	//     - Migrate remaining leaves (`solver/mixture_link`, `inference/probability`,
   258	//       `inference/generative`, `inference/sample`, `inference/formula_dsl`)
   259	//       upward to `solver/reml/runtime`, `solver/workflow`, `inference/model`.
   260	//

