   303	    /// native operator traces (notably sparse Cholesky) should override it.
   304	    ///
   305	    /// For HVP-only (implicit) operators on large problems we route
   306	    /// through Hutch++ — the Meyer–Musco split estimator achieves O(1/ε)
   307	    /// matvecs vs O(1/ε²) for plain Hutchinson, and avoids the O(p²)
   308	    /// memory + O(p) HVP cost of materializing the operator densely.
