     1	//! Canonical penalty pseudo-logdeterminant derivatives.
     2	//!
     3	//! This module provides a single, mathematically correct implementation of
     4	//! L(θ) = log|S(θ)|₊ and all its derivatives with respect to:
     5	//!
     6	//! - `ρ parameters` (log-lambda scaling): S(ρ) = Σ_k λ_k S_k, λ_k = e^{ρ_k}
     7	//! - `τ/ψ parameters` (design-moving): S depends on τ through the penalty
     8	//!   matrices themselves, not just through scalar scaling
     9	//! - `mixed ρ×τ` cross-derivatives
    10	//!
    11	//! # Mathematical foundation
    12	//!
    13	//! For a symmetric positive semidefinite penalty matrix S with eigendecomposition
    14	//! S = U Σ U^T, partition into positive and null eigenspaces:
    15	//!
    16	//! ```text
    17	//! S = U₊ Σ₊ U₊^T,   S⁺ = U₊ Σ₊⁻¹ U₊^T
    18	//! ```
    19	//!
    20	//! The pseudo-logdeterminant on the positive eigenspace is:
    21	//!
    22	//! ```text
    23	//! L = log|S|₊ = Σ_{σ_i > ε} log σ_i
    24	//! ```
    25	//!
    26	//! ## ρ-derivatives (fixed nullspace)
    27	//!
    28	//! For S(ρ) = Σ_k λ_k S_k where the nullspace N(S) = ∩_k N(S_k) is
    29	//! independent of ρ:
    30	//!
    31	//! ```text
    32	//! ∂_ρk L = λ_k tr(S⁺ S_k)
    33	//! ∂²_ρk ρl L = δ_{kl} ∂_ρk L − λ_k λ_l tr(S⁺ S_k S⁺ S_l)
    34	//! ```
    35	//!
    36	//! ## τ/ψ-derivatives (design-moving, fixed nullspace rank)
    37	//!
    38	//! For general parameter τ_i where S_{τ_i} = ∂S/∂τ_i:
    39	//!
    40	//! ```text
    41	//! ∂_τi L = tr(S⁺ S_{τ_i})
    42	//! ∂²_τi τj L = tr(S⁺ S_{τ_i τ_j}) − tr(S⁺ S_{τ_i} S⁺ S_{τ_j})
    43	//!              + 2 tr(Σ₊⁻² L_i L_j^T)           [moving-nullspace correction]
    44	//! ```
    45	//!
    46	//! where L_i = U₊^T S_{τ_i} U₀ is the leakage matrix from positive into null
    47	//! eigenspace.
    48	//!
    49	//! ## Computational approach
    50	//!
    51	//! A single eigendecomposition of S produces:
    52	//! - W factor: W (p × rank) with W W^T = S⁺, where W_{:,j} = u_j / √σ_j
    53	//! - Y_k = W^T S_k W (reduced-space representation): tr(S⁺ S_k) = tr(Y_k),
    54	//!   tr(S⁺ S_k S⁺ S_l) = tr(Y_k Y_l^T)
    55	//! - U₀ (null eigenvectors) and Σ₊⁻² for the moving-nullspace correction
